1 (i) Persons suspected of cheating.
2 (ii) Persons whose gaming privileges, permits, or licenses have been
3 suspended, revoked, or denied.
4 (iii) Persons who pose a threat to the safety of the patrons or employees of
5 the casino operator or casino manager or any casino gaming licensee.
6 (iv) Persons with a documented history of conduct involving the disruption
7 of the gaming operations in any jurisdiction.
8 (v) Persons subject to an order of a Louisiana court excluding such persons
9 from any gaming establishment.
10 (vi) Persons with pending charges for a gaming or gambling crime or a crime
11 related to the integrity of gaming operations.
12 (b) A person may not be excluded from a gaming establishment operated by
13 a licensee or the casino operator for reasons based solely on the skill level of the
14 person.
15 B. The board shall adopt rules to provide for the establishment of a list
16 of persons who are to be excluded from or ejected from a retail sports book and
17 from participating in the play or operation of mobile wagering pursuant to a
18 license or contract issued pursuant to the provisions of this Title. The rules shall
19 define the standards for exclusion or ejection and include standards relating to
20 the following persons:
21 (1) Those persons excluded as provided in Subsection A of this Section.
22 (2) Those persons who, before, during, or after a sporting event, threaten
23 violence or harm against any person who is involved in the sporting event,
24 where the threat is related to sports gaming.
25 (3) Those persons whose presence in a retail sports book or whose
26 participation in the play or operation of mobile wagering in this state is
27 determined by the board to pose a threat to the interests of the state, to
28 achieving the intents and purposes of this Title, or to the strict and effective
29 regulation of sports wagering.
30 C. The board and the division shall have the authority to place persons on the
