4 C.D. Whenever the name and description of any person is placed on an
5 excluded person's list pursuant to this Title, except at that person's request, the
6 division shall serve notice of such fact to such person by either of the following:
7 (1) By personal service.
8 (2) By certified mail to the last known address of such person.
9 D.E. A person may petition the board for removal of his name from the list.
10 The petitioner has the burden of proving he does not meet the criteria of Paragraph
11 (A)(1), (2), or (3) Subsection A of this Section.
12 E.F. Any person who has been placed on the list of persons to be excluded
13 or ejected from any gaming establishment pursuant to this Title may be imprisoned
14 for up to six months or fined not more than five hundred dollars, or both if he
15 thereafter enters or attempts to enter the premises of a gaming establishment without
16 first having obtained a determination by the board that he should not have been
17 placed on the list of persons to be excluded or ejected.
18 F.G. (1) The board may impose sanctions on a licensee, permittee, or casino
19 gaming operator under this Title, if the licensee, permittee, or casino gaming
20 operator willfully fails to exclude from the licensed gaming establishment a person
21 placed on the exclusion list.
22 (2) The board may seek revocation or suspension of a license, permit, or
23 casino operating contract if the licensee, permittee, or casino gaming operator
24 engages in a pattern of willful failure to exclude from the licensed gaming
25 establishment persons placed on the exclusion list.
26 G.H.(1) A person who is placed on the list is entitled to a hearing for review
27 of the listing, unless otherwise agreed by the board or division and the named person,
28 the hearing shall be held by the hearing officer in accordance with R.S. 27:25 not
29 later than thirty days after the receipt of the petition.
